30:49.360 --> 30:56.160
An outcome I see a conclusion of this, the idea that free software has become platformized

30:56.160 --> 31:01.880
and has become this sort of substrate, is a sort of two-tier society where we in this

31:01.880 --> 31:07.680
room are a sort of intelligentsia and we have access to these free tools and we get access

31:07.680 --> 31:09.400
to the four freedoms.

31:09.400 --> 31:16.400
We can use free software licensed products and we can study them, share them and improve

31:16.400 --> 31:17.400
them.

31:17.400 --> 31:22.640
Then we build services as a software substitute and everybody else is a kind of London proletariat

31:22.640 --> 31:28.720
who doesn't get those freedoms and doesn't get to sort of benefit in the intellectual

31:28.720 --> 31:31.880
fruits of free software.

31:31.880 --> 31:38.800
Is that necessarily connected to the kind of corporate capture of free and open source

31:38.800 --> 31:41.520
software that you were talking about?

31:41.520 --> 31:48.080
What are the organizational roots or the agitations that we can take to actually extend those

31:48.080 --> 31:53.640
freedoms out beyond the experts and to the people who use computers?

31:53.640 --> 31:54.640
