31:54.640 --> 31:59.520
A very big question you asked for sure.

31:59.520 --> 32:05.360
If we imagine the free software community, oftentimes we're very technical people.

32:05.360 --> 32:12.520
Like I use Linux desktop and I'm a social scientist so I would consider myself fairly

32:12.520 --> 32:13.840
non-technical here.

32:13.840 --> 32:21.040
But it allows us to have these sort of freedoms by having this technical knowledge.

32:21.040 --> 32:26.120
Many people, I'm sure many of you have interacted with, maybe don't have that technical knowledge

32:26.120 --> 32:32.400
or that capacity or whatever to sort of interact with free software in the same way and use

32:32.400 --> 32:36.560
it, maybe their job requires that they don't or whatever.

32:36.560 --> 32:45.600
And so does this play a part in sort of figuring out how we can advocate for these ideas to

32:45.600 --> 32:49.840
be more equitable across people?

32:49.840 --> 32:50.840
Is that correct?

32:50.840 --> 32:51.840
